Reasoning: The paper discusses the possibility of using computer vision for autonomous driving, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses privacy violations that may arise from autonomous driving, which falls under the computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper also talks about the constraint satisfaction problem and efficient solutions, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the social and political effects of autonomous driving, which falls under the social and information sciences (cs.SI) sub-category.
